**Overall meaning:**

This verse from the Upanishads describes the state of the soul (Atman) residing in the final ashram (stage of life) and attained enlightenment. It is a state of pure consciousness, free from sorrow and limitations, vast, infinite, and divine. It is the source of all creation and the ultimate reality. 
